gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Timberwolves 118, Wizards 107
gameRecap.excerpt: Minnesota defeats Washington, 118-107. Anthony Edwards led Minnesota with 38 points, along with five assists, and three rebounds as Karl-Anthony Towns (27 points, six rebounds) and Rudy Gobert (19 points, 16 rebounds, four blocks) totaled 46 points. Deni Avdiji led Washington with 24 points, six rebounds, and six assists as Marvin Bagley III added 17 points and a season-high 15 rebounds. Kyle Kuzma tallied 17 points, 14 rebounds, and eight assists for Washington in the loss. The Timberwolves snap a two-game skid and improve to 31-13 as the Wizards move to 7-36.
